Hi,

Currently every RibbonButton I have has an image and I would like to know if it is possible to rather than displaying an image for the ribbon button I can display a user control like (&lt;CustomWPFColorPicker:ColorPickerControlView x:Name=&quot;ForeColorPicker&quot; /&gt; )


Any help will be greatly appreciate it, as I am totally stuck

This is what I currenlty have:

&lt;r:RibbonButton Name=&quot;FontColor&quot; Margin=&quot;0,10,0,0&quot; Command=&quot;{StaticResource FontColorCommand}&quot;&gt;


&lt;r:RibbonCommand x:Key=&quot;FontColorCommand&quot;
                             ToolTipTitle=&quot;Font Color&quot;
                             ToolTipDescription=&quot;Changes the text color.&quot; 
                             SmallImageSource=&quot;Images/Forecolor.gif&quot;
                             LargeImageSource=&quot;Images/Forecolor.gif&quot;
                             CanExecute=&quot;FontColorRibbonCommand_CanExecute&quot;
                             Executed=&quot;FontColorRibbonCommand_Executed&quot;/&gt;

Thanks
